e walking along to one of our missions and I'm tabbing stuff and happen to see a delirious merek; my heart fills with joy.  I get my friend to teach me Taming 3 right there and now I can actually get it.  I store my pets and move in to catch it.<br>
<br>
I spent, literally, HOURS trying to catch it.  There were times when my entire combat log was filled with &quot;You failed to tame the creature.&quot;  Atleast twice I went in to catch it with a freshly masked scent and tried so many times that it took long enough for my mask to wear off and I had to remask.  He would not stop darting around going outside my taming area too, he was just impossible to catch.  He aggrod on me plenty of times, we ran around, he gave up, i would try again.  After about my 200th try or so he glitched and his name went from red (aggro) to the light purple color (faction pet) but he wasn't in my DP.  I check the radial menu, I got the Tame option still, but now I couldn't attack him, like he was a pet.  In the end a nearby assassin saw me, I didn't even bother to stand up, he came over and killed me.  And THEN because the delirious one was now my color he and the harvester near by came over and killed the baby delirious.  I spent hours of the most frustrating experience of my life to come away with nothing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=orist@creaturehandlersofswg>Orist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#70DB93>(9/30/03 3:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: @#$^@$</span><hr size=1> Ack!  I think I would be plenty pissed at that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Was at home eating lunch today, decided to check to see how big my GSP's had grown, was in the middle of a big grassy plain east of Coronet...  Low and behold a grand wrix family about 100-150 meters out.  First try I got a grand wrix baby, I was so happy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Good luck on the mereks, I get scared jus being near them much less trying to tame one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alladdim>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#70DB93>(10/1/03 2:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: @#$^@$</span><hr size=1> There are a LOT of mereks near the Research outpost on Endor. Not to mention you get merek lair missions very easily on the mission terminals. You should see those toxic merek battlelords fight. They hit for 500-600s and run really really fast (like a GSP). Mereks are great pets and I think pretty much all mid-high lvl CH have at least one of those. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cobragt18>cobragt18</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img1.ranchoweb.com/images/cobragt18/pirate-swordclear.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#70DB93>(10/2/03 8:05 am)</fo